As an approved AP on the PwD Catalog Portal,
I want to upload details, images, and specifications of my product through an easy-to-use submission form,
so that PwDs visiting the catalog can view accurate and engaging information about my product and determine if it meets their accessibility needs.
 
Acceptance Criteria
1.	Access to Product Upload
o	The AP can access the “Product Upload” option from the AP Dashboard.
o	Product upload is a tab selection in available in 4 tabs and have a dedicated section.
2.	Following are the sections in “Upload New Product” flow.
3.	Basic Product Information
o	The form includes the following mandatory fields:
	Product Name
	Product Type - Device or Technology
	Disability type- Mobility, Visual, Hearing, Speech, Cognitive, Multiple Disabilities
	Disability percentage- 0-40%, 40-60%, 60-80%, 80-100%, All Ranges
	Short Description (appears as summary text on the catalog listing card; limited to ~200 characters)- Along with option to generate with Gen AI “Assist with GenAI”
	Detailed Description (appears on the product details page when a PwD user clicks the product)- Along with option to generate with Gen AI “Assist with GenAI”- refer Scrum-21 as well.
o	Text fields support basic formatting (bullet points, paragraphs).
4.	Product’s Unique Feature- Text box to describe unique feature of product, along with help icon to guide the vendor and with a option to generate with Gen AI “Assist with GenAI”- refer Figma. also covered in detail in Scrum- 32.
5.	Buying Guide- For AP to add buying guide (with Gen AI assist) for PWDs- refer Figma.
6.	Product Images- Also refer Scrum-23
o	Vendors can upload:
	One primary image (this appears as the thumbnail or highlighted image on the catalog card).
	Up to 5 additional images showcasing product angles, usage, packaging, etc.
o	Accepted formats: JPG, PNG.
o	File size (5 MB) and dimension guidelines are clearly stated.
o	Preview thumbnails are displayed for all uploaded images.
o	Vendor can remove or replace any uploaded image before submission.
o	Include tips and help icons to guide Vendor user- refer Figma.
o	All Images should have option to add Alt Text including Primary image.
7.	3D Mockup Images - maximum 3 images. Include Image tip- Refer Figma.
8.	Demo Video- Also refer Scrum-23
o	An optional field allows upload of a demo video file or embedding of a YouTube/Vimeo link.
o	The video appears on the detailed product page in same media carousel.
o	Video uploads are limited by file size and duration (as per platform policy).
o	Include tips and help icons to guide Vendor user- refer Figma.
9.	Specifications Section
o	A structured section is provided for Technical and Accessibility Specifications, e.g.:
	Dimensions
	Weight
	Material / Build Type
	Power or Battery requirements (if applicable)
	Accessibility features (voice control, tactile feedback, adjustable design, etc.)
o	Fields can be free-text or key-value pairs, depending on design.
o	“Generate Specifications”- GenAI assisted specifications.
10.	Geographical Availability
o	Vendor can specify availability as either:
	“Pan-India” if product is available in entire country.
	Search list of available geographies (e.g., states or cities).
o	Multiple selections are allowed when “Specific Areas” is chosen.- refer Figma
11.	Product Quantity
o	Vendor can enter available quantity (numeric field).
o	Optionally, a toggle for “Made to Order” if inventory is not fixed.
o	Quantity updates should be editable later from the product management screen.
12.	Additional Information- refer scrum- 26 as well
o	Amazon Buy Link
o	Product Website Link
o	Price Range- with toggle-Exact price/Price range- refer Figma
o	For exact price- one numeric field to enter amount in rupees.
o	For Price range- two fields Max and Min- refer Figma.
o	Tags/Metadata
o	Other Links
13.	Save as Draft-
o	Vendor after filling all the details can also save the product as draft, using “Save as Draft button” available on left side of “Upload Product” button.
o	In Draft product should also be visible in product management page in order to edit and upload the product finally.
o	In draft product will not go for admin review.
14.	Form Validation and Feedback
o	All mandatory fields are validated before submission.
o	Image and video file type/size checks occur before upload completion.
o	On successful submission, vendor receives an on-screen confirmation message such as:
“Your product has been submitted for review and will be published after approval.”
o	An automated email confirmation is sent to the vendor.
15.	Admin Workflow
o	Submitted product enters “Pending Review” status in the admin dashboard.
o	Admins can review, approve, or reject with comments.
o	Once approved, the product becomes visible on the public PwD catalog page.
16.	Accessibility & UI Compliance
o	All labels, buttons, and media fields meet WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards.
o	Each image field supports alternative text entry for screen readers.
o	The form supports keyboard navigation and visual focus indicators.
17.	Performance and System Handling
o	Images and video uploads use progress indicators.
o	Incomplete uploads or failed submissions show user-friendly error messages.

